This is a short 2D platformer game project named ludo anni.

The language used was python with the help of the python modules from Pygame and the compiler used was VisualStudioCode.
It's a simple platformer with 3 Dirction Keys where the goal is to collect all 17 coins that are found in the one and only level.
The game was made as our school project in our labratory subject.

+-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
How to Run: 	The main file is called "game.py", be sure to execute this file via your perferred compiler, 
		and be sure you have the latest python and pygame isntallation.
+-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+

+-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
Controlls:	A or Left_Arrow_Key: Move Left
		D or Right_Arrow_Key: Move Right
		W or Space or Up_Arrow_Key: Jump
+-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+

+-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
Features:	Free Player Tracking Cam
		Downwards Volocity
		Entity Collision
		Pixel Based Sprites
		Background Music and misc. sfx
		Main Menu Screen
		Object Oriented
+-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+

